node.text: “It looks like a paper plate with a face on it!” In a new episode of our Cartoon Challenge, @aparnapkin draws a New Yorker cartoon, and drafts her very own caption, with the help of the expert @willmcphail4. Feel free to compliment her artistry in the comments below. (Do *not* mention the ghouls!)

node.title: Aparna Nancherla Tries to Keep Up With a New Yorker Cartoonist

node.text:
Another week, another chance at fame and fortune. Enter the contest by leaving your funniest caption in the comments below, with the hashtag #MyNewYorkerCaption.

Finalists for this week’s cartoon, by P. C. Vey, will appear online September 14th and in the September 20, 2021, issue of the magazine. You must be over 13 to officially enter. Only one submission with the hashtag per username is permitted. Tap the link in our bio for the full contest rules.
